Can we improve our brain? Make it better?
Yes we can, believe it or not.
Imagine brains: your brains, the brains of anyone, can increase its
productivity.
10 % more, 30 % more, 50 % or even 80 % or more.
Would that change your life? How different would your life be?!!
======(dit bovenstaande als blikvanger, om interesse op te wekken
verder te lezen.
Daarna een verdere stap: wie zit er achter? ==========
The team that discovered that we can indeed enlarge the capacity of
our brains. Everyone’s.
A group of brain performance expert-scientists have found out how. They
compared 20 years of research of EEG (brain wave patterns) research
on a method to easily improve a person’s brain functioning. Easily yes.
Without any effort. That anyone can do.
No: no medication needed, not by using drugs. Not by implants. No
change of lifestyle needed: no believe or conviction needed even. One
practices by sitting comfortably with the eyes closed and practice
mentally, at home or at the office.
They claim to have found a very efficient, easy to practice method, to
make one’s brain perform much more efficient, starting to use its full
potential. And then increase creativity, intelligence, understanding things
quicker, absorb information faster. And: Make one more stress resilient.
Applicable to everyone, and to every organization that wants to cope with
burnout, fatigue, underperformance. Or for organisations searching
clever brains to employ, facing stiff competition, thus prepare for
innovative, game-changing technologies.
Our offer
When you consider to introduce the method to the employees
working in your organization, our proposal includes to assemble an

initial sufficient large group of people. Than measure the brainwave
patterns (EEG) of each person before they get the instruction in the
method, and again 3 months after the instruction.
Then show some significant changes have taken place, such as the
appearance of special frequencies that indicate more wellbeing, restful
alertness. Better integration, interaction, of different parts of the brain.

